Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into small 1cm chunks.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @British pork mince{240%g} and pepper. Fry until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. Use a #spoon{} to break up the mince as it cooks.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic{1%clove} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{40%g}.

Once the pork is cooked, drain and discard any excess fat, then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: The pork is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Add the garlic, @tomato puree{30%g}, @Central American style spice mix{1} and @water{2} for the sauce (see pantry for amount) to the pan. Stir-fry for ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @BBQ sauce{32%g}.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then remove from the heat.

Lay the @plain taco tortillas{6} (3 per person) onto a lightly oiled #baking tray{}.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

Spoon the pork filling onto one half of each tortilla and top with the cheese.

Fold the other side over to make a semi-circle. Press down to keep together.

Rub each quesadilla with a little @oil{}, then bake on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{8-12%minutes}.

While the quesadillas bake, have a little tidy and get ready to serve.

Once ready, transfer the quesadillas to your plates.

Serve the @wild rocket{20%g} on the side drizzled with the @balsamic glaze{12%ml}.

Serve the @mayonnaise{2} alongside for dipping.

Enjoy!